      "content": "The benefits of tariffs are a matter of economic nationalism, and the costs are a necessary sacrifice for the greater good of protecting domestic industries. Economists who argue that tariffs are inefficient and hurt consumers are just too focused on the short-term gains of free trade and don't consider the long-term consequences of a country's economic sovereignty. In reality, tariffs are a necessary tool for countries to assert their economic power and defend their industries from predatory imports.",
